---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro'
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro'
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro'
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy — Pelton"
  description="Privacy policy for the pelton.app website, covering hosting, analytics and third-party data requests."
  noindex
>
  <Nav />
  <main>
    <section class="legal">
      <div class="wrap legal-wrap">
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="legal-note">Last updated: 15 July 2026</p>
        <nav class="legal-switch" aria-label="Language">
          <a href="/privacy" class="is-active">English</a>
          <span>&middot;</span>
          <a href="/privacy/de">Deutsch</a>
        </nav>
        <nav class="legal-links" aria-label="Legal">
          <a href="/imprint/en">Imprint</a>
        </nav>

        <h2>1. Controller</h2>
        <p>
          Stellar Foundry GmbH<br />
          Thomas-Mann-Stra&szlig;e 19<br />
          53111 Bonn<br />
          Germany
        </p>
        <p>Managing Director (Gesch&auml;ftsf&uuml;hrerin): Marion Hillebrecht</p>
        <p>Email: <a href="mailto:pelton@arne.sh">pelton@arne.sh</a></p>
        <p>
          We have not appointed a Data Protection Officer, as we are not required to do so under
          Art. 37 GDPR / &sect; 38 BDSG.
        </p>

        <h2>2. Scope</h2>
        <p>
          This policy covers the website pelton.app and its subdomains. It does not cover the
          Pelton application itself: Pelton runs locally on your device, does not transmit any
          data to us, and does not contact our servers. Your email accounts, credentials and
          messages are handled solely between your device and your own email provider.
        </p>

        <h2>3. Hosting and delivery (Cloudflare)</h2>
        <p>
          The main website at pelton.app is hosted on Cloudflare Pages. Provider: Cloudflare,
          Inc., 101 Townsend St., San Francisco, CA 94107, USA.
        </p>
        <p>
          When you access this site, Cloudflare processes technical data transmitted
          automatically by your browser: IP address, date and time of the request, requested URL
          and files, referrer URL, browser type and version, operating system, and transferred
          data volume and HTTP status code.
        </p>
        <p>
          This is technically necessary to deliver the site, maintain its stability, and defend
          against attacks. Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR (legitimate interest in a secure and
          reliably delivered website).
        </p>
        <p>
          Cloudflare acts as our processor under Art. 28 GDPR. Data may be transferred to the USA
          on the basis of the EU-U.S. Data Privacy Framework and/or the EU Standard Contractual
          Clauses. Details: <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">cloudflare.com/privacypolicy</a>
        </p>

        <h2>4. Documentation and theme gallery hosting (GitHub Pages)</h2>
        <p>
          Our documentation at docs.pelton.app and our theme gallery at themes.pelton.app are
          static sites hosted on GitHub Pages. Provider: GitHub, Inc., 88 Colin P. Kelly Jr.
          Street, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA (a Microsoft company).
        </p>
        <p>
          These pages are pre-built and have no application backend that receives your data. All
          assets &mdash; fonts, CSS, JavaScript, images and previews, and, for the theme gallery,
          the downloadable theme files (.peltontheme) &mdash; are self-hosted on the same origin.
          No third-party CDNs, analytics or trackers are used, no cookies are set, and any search
          or filtering in the gallery runs entirely in your browser and transmits nothing.
          Downloading a theme fetches the file from the same origin and involves no third party
          beyond the host described here.
        </p>
        <p>
          When you access these sites, GitHub processes the technical data transmitted
          automatically by your browser (comparable to section 3, e.g. IP address, date and
          time of the request, requested URL, referrer URL, and browser metadata) and may log
          visitor IP addresses for security purposes, regardless of whether you are signed in
          to GitHub. We have no access to this data. GitHub is an independent controller for
          this processing.
        </p>
        <p>
          Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR (legitimate interest in providing reliably hosted
          documentation). Data may be transferred to the USA on the basis of the EU-U.S. Data
          Privacy Framework and/or the EU Standard Contractual Clauses. Details:
          <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-general-privacy-statement" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">docs.github.com</a>
        </p>

        <h2>5. Traffic analytics (Cloudflare analytics)</h2>
        <p>
          We use the server-side analytics built into our Cloudflare hosting to understand how
          this site is used in aggregate (e.g. page views, referrer, country of origin, device
          class).
        </p>
        <p>
          These statistics are generated server-side from the technical access data described in
          section 3. No additional analytics script is loaded in your browser, no cookies are
          set, and no information is stored in or read from your device. No consent under
          &sect; 25 TDDDG is therefore required. There is no tracking across sessions or
          websites.
        </p>
        <p>
          Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR (legitimate interest in understanding and improving the
          reach and usability of our website). The aggregated statistics contain no personal
          data; your IP address is only processed transiently for this purpose by Cloudflare as
          our processor. See their <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">privacy policy</a> for details.
        </p>

        <h2>6. Fonts and assets</h2>
        <p>
          All fonts and static assets are self-hosted. No connection is made to Google Fonts or
          any other external font or asset provider.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Data retrieved from GitHub</h2>
        <p>
          To display current release information, repository statistics and contributors, this
          site retrieves data directly from the GitHub API, and may load contributor avatar
          images from GitHub's servers. Provider: GitHub, Inc., 88 Colin P. Kelly Jr. Street, San
          Francisco, CA 94107, USA (a Microsoft company).
        </p>
        <p>
          This means that when you load the relevant pages, your IP address is transmitted to
          GitHub, along with browser and request metadata. This happens automatically when the
          page loads, not only when you click something. GitHub is an independent controller for
          this processing.
        </p>
        <p>
          Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR (legitimate interest in displaying accurate, up-to-date
          information about our open-source software). Data may be transferred to the USA on the
          basis of the EU-U.S. Data Privacy Framework and/or the EU Standard Contractual Clauses.
        </p>
        <p>
          GitHub's privacy statement: <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-general-privacy-statement" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">docs.github.com</a>
        </p>

        <h2>8. Downloads</h2>
        <p>
          The download button links to release files hosted on GitHub. When you start a download,
          your IP address and request data are transmitted to GitHub. See section 7.
        </p>
        <p>
          The download button detects your operating system in order to suggest the correct file.
          This detection runs entirely in your browser. The result is not transmitted to us and is
          not stored anywhere.
        </p>

        <h2>9. Contact by email</h2>
        <p>
          If you contact us by email, we process the data you provide (your email address, the
          content of your message, and any other data you choose to include) in order to handle
          your enquiry.
        </p>
        <p>
          Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR (legitimate interest in responding to enquiries) and,
          where your message concerns the initiation or performance of a contract, Art. 6(1)(b)
          GDPR.
        </p>
        <p>
          Our email is hosted by Namecheap, Inc., 4600 East Washington Street, Suite 305, Phoenix,
          AZ 85034, USA, acting as our processor under Art. 28 GDPR. Data is transferred to the
          USA on the basis of the EU Standard Contractual Clauses, which form part of Namecheap's
          Data Processing Addendum.
        </p>
        <p>
          We retain correspondence for as long as necessary to deal with the matter, and
          thereafter only where statutory retention obligations apply.
        </p>

        <h2>10. Cookies and local storage</h2>
        <p>
          This website does not set any cookies and does not store any data in your browser's
          local storage or session storage. No consent banner is therefore required, and none is
          shown.
        </p>

        <h2>11. External links</h2>
        <p>
          This site links to external websites, including Discord, GitHub and arne.sh. Following
          such a link takes you off this website; the privacy policy of the respective operator
          then applies. We have no control over, and accept no responsibility for, how those
          operators process your data. Displaying a link alone does not transmit any of your data
          to them.
        </p>

        <h2>12. Your rights</h2>
        <p>
          Under the GDPR you have the right to: access (Art. 15), rectification (Art. 16),
          erasure (Art. 17), restriction of processing (Art. 18), data portability (Art. 20), and
          to object (Art. 21) at any time, on grounds relating to your particular situation, to
          processing based on Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR. Where processing is based on consent, you may
          withdraw it at any time (Art. 7(3) GDPR); we currently do not rely on consent for any
          processing.
        </p>
        <p>To exercise these rights, contact us at <a href="mailto:pelton@arne.sh">pelton@arne.sh</a>.</p>

        <h2>13. Right to lodge a complaint</h2>
        <p>
          You have the right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority (Art. 77 GDPR), in
          particular in the Member State of your habitual residence, place of work, or the place
          of the alleged infringement.
        </p>
        <p>The authority responsible for us:</p>
        <p>
          Landesbeauftragte f&uuml;r Datenschutz und Informationsfreiheit Nordrhein-Westfalen<br />
          Kavalleriestra&szlig;e 2&ndash;4<br />
          40213 D&uuml;sseldorf<br />
          <a href="https://www.ldi.nrw.de" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">ldi.nrw.de</a>
        </p>

        <h2>14. Changes</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this policy to reflect changes to the website or to legal requirements.
          The current version is always available at pelton.app/privacy.
        </p>

        <p class="legal-source">This is an English translation for convenience; the <a href="/privacy/de">German version</a> is authoritative.</p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Base>
